Years of poor oyster harvests have waterman Bill Beck worried about the future of the industry.
Recently, he and his family harvested nearly 4,000 bushels of disease-free oysters from managed reserves.
Environmentalists are frustrated with the slow progress in cleaning up the Chesapeake Bay, leading to legal action against the EPA.
Nutria, an invasive species, are causing economic damage and efforts are underway to eradicate them.
The decline in oyster population and water quality in the bay is a growing concern, prompting calls for better management and conservation efforts.
